The Agility Ladder: Misconceptions and the Truth

 Coach Bres June 14, 2017 Athletics,  Coaching,  Football,  Speed & Agility Leave a Comment

One of the most widely used – and misunderstood – athletic training tools is the agility ladder. For years, we have seen athletes of every sport attack the ladder every day in a vain attempt to get faster and more agile. Problem is, that’s not really what the ladder does. Performing ladder drills won’t improve your speed or agility in … 
