The Squat: Range of Motion Before Weight

 Coach Bres May 22, 2017 Athletics,  Coaching,  Football,  Instructional,  Mobility,  Teaching Leave a Comment

One of the biggest issues we see on a regular basis is athletes sacrificing depth and form during the back squat in favor of loading up the bar with heavy weight. By shutting down the range of motion to just a partial squat, athletes are minimizing many of the intended benefits that can come from improving baseline strength. First, they eliminate one … 
